The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Academy plans in place
                                                                                                                                                                                                     Academy plans in place
            A STAFF REPORTER                      
	Calcutta: If everything falls into place, the dream of an Indian playing for a German club in the Bundesliga is not too distant.         
	On Thursday, while announcing their plans to set up the first Bayern Munich Academy outside Germany  the Bengal Techno Bayern Munich Academy in Burdwan  chairman Karl Heinz Rummenigge said: Our philosophy in partnership is different from that of many other clubs in Europe. They are going to China, Japan mainly to make money. We are thinking differently.         
	In 2005, our junior team came here and won the IFA Shield... And in May Oliver Kahn played his last match here. We are thinking different You never know, may be in the future we will see a professional from the academy playing for Bayern Munich in the Bundesliga.         
	Announcing their blueprint for India, Rummenigge said: We want to develop young players in the country... We want India to become a powerhouse in Asia. We may bring young coaches from Germany to educate and show the youngsters here how football is being run in Europe.         
	Talking about Bayerns plans about the proposed academy in Burdwan, the 53-year old said: Plans are afoot to hold age-group tournaments and have floodlit artificial turfs so that football can be played round the year. There will also be a team of physiosand trainers to look after the medical aspect.         
	Though the details are yet to be worked out the estimated cost of the project would be Rs 23 crore and would start by next season.         
	The German great, later in the evening, also met Indian football team captain Bhaichung Bhutia and the legendary P.K. Banerjee at a function.         
	Rummenigge also met chief minister Buddhadeb Bhattacharjee for a brief while at Writers Buildings.         
	It was a very satisfactory meeting with the chief minister. He was very happy that Bayern Munich would set up the academy in this state. He told us to concentrate on the coaching aspect, Rummenigge said.                                                                                                                          
